	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload">
		<text>Ammo Loader (sequential load)</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_title">
		<text>Ammo Loader (sequential load)</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_key_toggle">
		<text>Preset / load-under-cursor key</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_key_toggle_desc">
		<text>When no GUI is open, opens the sequential load preset configuration window. When the inventory is open and the cursor hovers a magazine, triggers sequential loading of that magazine.</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_debug_header">
		<text>Debug</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_debug">
		<text>Debug (ammo order dump tools)</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_debug_desc">
		<text>When enabled, the following options work: dump key in the inventory (magazine under cursor) and outside the inventory (magazine in the weapon in hand) according to the modifier below. When disabled, key bind is ignored. Preset/sequential load on U is not affected.</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_key_dump">
		<text>Dump key (debug)</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_key_dump_desc">
		<text>Only active when Debug is on. In inventory, shows round order in the magazine under the cursor. Outside inventory, shows round order in the magazine in the hand weapon (use modifier as below). Default: middle mouse. MCM cannot bind to mouse1/2/3 in the UI, but keyboard and mouse4+ are allowed.</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_dump_weapon_modifier">
		<text>Hand weapon: modifier (debug)</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_dump_weapon_modifier_desc">
		<text>With inventory closed, which key must be held with the dump key. None: dump key alone. Default: Shift.</text>
	</string>

	<string id="st_seqload_dump_empty">
		<text>Magazine is empty</text>
	</string>

	<string id="st_seqload_dump_round">
		<text>%s - %dx</text>
	</string>

	<string id="st_seqload_dump_more">
		<text>...</text>
	</string>

	<string id="st_seqload_dump_no_mag">
		<text>No magazine attached</text>
	</string>

	<string id="st_seqload_dump_remainder_header">
		<text>Remainder:</text>
	</string>

	<!-- MCM list/radio: path seqload/dump_weapon_modifier, value 0-3 -->
	<string id="seqload_dump_weapon_modifier_lst_seqload_mod_none">
		<text>None (dump key only)</text>
	</string>

	<string id="seqload_dump_weapon_modifier_lst_seqload_mod_shift">
		<text>Shift</text>
	</string>

	<string id="seqload_dump_weapon_modifier_lst_seqload_mod_ctrl">
		<text>Ctrl</text>
	</string>

	<string id="seqload_dump_weapon_modifier_lst_seqload_mod_alt">
		<text>Alt</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_instant_load">
		<text>Instant loading</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_instant_load_desc">
		<text>If enabled - the whole magazine is loaded instantly. If disabled - rounds are loaded one by one with delay and sound, matching vanilla Anomaly Magazines Redux behavior. Disabled by default.</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_ignore_bad_ammo">
		<text>Ignore damaged ammo</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_ignore_bad_ammo_desc">
		<text>If enabled - ammo with _bad and _verybad suffix (damaged) is hidden from the preset configuration menu and is not loaded into magazines. Enabled by default.</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_tooltip_ammo_types">
		<text>Magazine tooltip: ammo types</text>
	</string>

	<string id="ui_mcm_seqload_tooltip_ammo_types_desc">
		<text>If enabled, the magazine item tooltip shows a &quot;Type:&quot; section with how many rounds of each ammo type are inside, between the loaded count and &quot;Round on top&quot; (or before the detailed round list). Colours match the default Mags Redux tooltip. Enabled by default.</text>
	</string>

	<string id="st_seqload_tooltip_type_header">
		<text>Type:</text>
	</string>

